commit e3f28358edd6ca60e7007b39caed6c376f324913
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 13:45:13 2026 -0400

    feat(cms)(per-page-content): widen ContentScope to page/form; per-object DraftEditor reconciliation

    Branch 5.2 (ADR 0008): the DraftEditor's draft/published reconciliation now
    generalizes over ANY content object addressed by its scope, proven before any
    route migrates.

    - ContentScope widens from the single 'site' inhabitant to a closed union over
      site | page | form. PageScope/FormScope carry a closed PageId/FormId and are
      generic in the id so load/writes return the precise per-object content type.
    - New pages/registry: the single source mapping each closed PageId/FormId to its
      schema + bundled default + derived draft/published storage keys
      (content/pages/<page>(.draft).json, forms/<form>(.draft).json). scopeKeys, the
      read path (5.3), and the admin sections (5.5) all resolve through it.
    - DraftEditor.load/editDocument/applyImageUpload/applyListOps/publish route
      through resolveScope -> a per-scope ScopeCodec bundle (key pair + draft/publish
      codecs + default). The reconciliation algorithm did not fork; only the bundle
      varies per scope. Site keeps its laxer DraftSiteContent draft + id-backfill;
      pages/forms decode strictly (no id-only-add flow yet).
    - Delete the now-orphaned Content.AdminContent/AdminContentSource (load returns
      the scope-generic Loaded<S> instead); migrate the route comment.
    - Tests: per-object scopeKeys (page/form, no collisions); per-object load
      reconciliation (defaults/published/draft-no-published/draft-newer/stale);
      page edit -> reopen -> publish -> live object; per-object blast-radius
      isolation (a FAQ edit never touches content/site.json); form scope round-trip.

